SIMPLE: unstop
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unstop
<hw>Un*stop"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>stop</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To take the stopple or stopper from; <as>as, to
<ex>unstop</ex> a bottle or a cask</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To free from any obstruction; to open.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unstrain</ent>⟦br⟧
